summary:
Goal-oriented, quick learner, and proactive solo and team player. Professional with 17 years of experience.  Looking for an opportunity within Information Technologies, Television, Media, Telecom industries. Ready for substantial business travel.

Specialties and expertise:
— Pre-Sales, Telecom Solutions and Processes;
— Business Model Analysis, Business Process Analysis, Requirements Analysis;
— Enterprise Architecture, Information Systems Architecture and Design;
— Software Development Technologies and Practices;
— Systems Integration Design;
— TV Everywhere, Multiscreen and OTT TV, LTE Broadcasting, Telecom VAS Solutions; Telecom Service Layer, IMS services, OSS and BSS integration, Service-Aware Charging, Traffic Optimization Solutions;
— Usability, User Interface Design, Information Architecture.


Proficiency:
— Information Systems Integration and Solution Design; Delivery Services Analysis, Estimation and Planning; Product and Solution Customization and Adaptations; Technical Impact Analysis, Gap Analysis;
— Interactive TV End-to-End Architecture and Solutions, IPTV, OTT TV, Hybrid TV, TV Broadcasting Head-End Architecture, Content Delivery Networks (CDN), Conditional Access Systems (CAS), Digital Rights Management Systems (DRM), Content Management Systems (CMS);
— Business Process Design, Product Design;
— Service-Aware Charging, Charging Data Mediation; Mobile Positioning Systems (MPS), Location Based Services (LBS); Mobile Packet Networks User Experience Optimization.

profile_positions.description:
— Performed Technical Solution Sales and Business Development role within TV and Media Management sales organization for the market region spanning Scandinavian, Baltic, CIS and Central Asian countries, Mongolia;
— Led to winning several end-to-end TV solutions' new sale, up-sell and upgrade project contracts, worth of several million USD
— Designed and supervised the delivery of the commercial end-to-end Interactive TV solutions, now serving hundreds of thousands of end-users, tens of thousands of simultaneous on-demand unicast video streaming sessions, and many hundreds of broadcast/multicast TV channels;
— Performed numerous commercial and non-commercial TV and Media solutions-related (OTT TV, Hybrid TV, Mobile Packet Network Traffic and User Experience Optimization) customer demonstrations, proof of concepts and trials;
— Took lead for customer opportunities engagements and development as Technical Solution Responsible, starting from «the initial call»;
— Prepared and participated in the customers' and partners' C-level meetings for negotiations, presentations and workshops on all stages of the Sales Life Cycle;
— Solicited and identified customer implicit and explicit needs, transformed the gathered inputs into customer solutions;
— Worked close to customers' technical stakeholders on the deployed solutions' life-cycle management, development, updates and upgrades;
— Acted as Customer Solution Responsible for RFx responses preparation and follow-up engagements, prepared technical solution materials (High-Level Solution Design, Dimensioning Model, Bill of Materials, Statements of Compliance, Accptance Testing Protocol and Criteria; inputs for Low-Level Design, Responsibility Matrix, Services Description, Statements of Work, Time-Plan, etc. documents);
— Represented Ericsson products and solutions at road-shows and industry trade events and conferences (IBC, CSTB, local venues, etc.)

— Took key driving Technical Customer Solution Responsible role in winning new-to-the-market-region commercial contracts for end-to-end Interactive TV solutions, worth of several million USD;
— Took part in customer and partner C-level meetings for technical requirements negotiations and solution presentations;
— Worked close to customers' technical stakeholders on supporting and improving upon deployed solutions;
— Led technical responses to customer RFx, prepared technical solution materials and services-related inputs for commercial offerings;
— Performed customer business requirements transformation into systems' architecture and design;
— Was responsible for design and delivery of a number of customer technical solutions within domains of Service Aware Charging, BSS, Mobile Positioning Systems, Location Based Services and Interactive TV Solutions;
— Performed a number of commercial and non-commercial Service-Aware Charging and Interactive TV customer trials and proof of concept projects involving integration to live customer network and services environments.

— Performed business analysis, requirements solicitation, internal (Billing, Financial Control and Receivables) and third party (Portmone.com) systems and API's integration analysis, definition and design — all to define and develop the new information system's architecture with low-level design documentation for the subject of On-line personal mobile account top-up payment system; performed validation, feed-backing, evaluating and acceptance testing of the third-party (outsourcing SW development company) produced code for the system;
— Defined and developed requirements for the RFP on Web-based CMS System;
— Evaluated participants of GSM Network Upgrade to Convergent Next Generation Network Architecture Tender;
— Defined and developed requirements and architecture for Media portal solution;
— Defined and developed requirements for IPTV system;
— Mentored new employees for quick dive in into the roles and tasks;
— Participated in refinement of existing internal software development and requirements management processes.

— Developed interface design and its specifications for the in-house data management systems based upon Intranet technologies (Internet Explorer 5.5-6.0 front-end and PHP 4-5/Oracle 9i back-end);
— Implemented HTML, DHTML, JavaScript, XSLT, Visual Basic 6.0, SQL and PHP coding for the following Intranet core systems: Work Order, Trouble Ticket, Personnel, Document Directory, Buildings, Clients, Contacts, and many others;
— Developed and programmed a number of reusable web-client components (calendars, tool-bars, menu systems, etc.);
— Performed various internal systems' reports prototyping using XML and XSL;
Developed XML Schemas for data structures;
— Written technical documentation to the developed systems and tools;
— Worked with team of developers to ensure consistency between layout design (my responsibility) and code development stages of the company's Intranet system;
— Designed graphics and templates for presentations;
— Designed graphical user interfaces, icons, and documentation illustrations for the company’s Intranet System, Data Management System, Workflow, Human Resource Management and Accounting Systems based on the MS Access 2000 front-end and MS SQL Server back-end technologies.

— Developed front-end components design for client-server 3-layer based — web browser client, PHP application server and Oracle RDBMS — application architecture for the Intranet applications, namely: Trouble Tickets, Personnel, Document Management, and others;
— Designed and Implemented web and native applications GUI;
— Designed ad-hoc graphics, illustrations for various technical documents and electronic systems;
— Written technical documentation on the GUI design standards and the implemented Intranet systems.

— Designed and coded a number of Web-sites and interactive applications for various customers: political parties, non-profit organizations, artists, etc;
— Designed customer companies' identity (logos, documents, business cards, etc);
— Performed from-idea-to-realization process for client's posters, brochures, web-site layouts, etc.

— Defined concept and information design model for the Institute's web site;
— Performed graphics design for the new web-site;
— Implemented the new web-site's templates in coding.
